HEADWORD: Toccata
<hw>Toc*ca"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It., fr.
<ets>toccare</ets> to touch. See <er>Touch</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An old form of piece for the organ or
harpsichord, somewhat in the free and brilliant style of the
<xex>prelude</xex>, <xex>fantasia</xex>, or
<xex>capriccio</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

